In this week’s episode of the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts revisit one of the most beloved Superman stories of all time: All Star Superman by Grant Morrison and Frank Quitely! With James Gunn’s Superman film just days away, we take a deep dive into the comic that helped redefine the Man of Steel for a modern era and reportedly inspired Gunn’s take on the character. We break down the emotional, philosophical, and mythological weight of the 12-issue epic, explore how it celebrates everything iconic about Superman, and debate which moments might find their way to the big screen. Whether you're a longtime fan or discovering the story for the first time, this is the perfect prep before Clark Kent returns to theaters! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

